    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "RSI Momentum Zone",
      "explanation_en": "The Relative Strength Index (RSI) measures how fast a stock's price is moving on a scale of 0\u2013100. A reading between 55\u201370 is the 'bullish momentum zone' \u2014 the stock has strong buying pressure without being dangerously overbought. Today's best picks (MTN, CVLT, NOK) all sit in this zone, while many other screener candidates with RSI above 70 were passed over because overbought stocks often pull back sharply.",
